frameDefinitions: This frame is about Items in the state of occupying a certain Rank within a hierarchy.
An Agent disables a flying or floating Patient, causing it to be unable to support itself in its current medium.
This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
A Speaker addresses an Audience on a particular Topic.
Criteria exist that identify a particular Subset of a Group of things into members and non-members.
The Focal_feature is defined in relation to a Landmark_feature, either as a particular part, or as an immediately bordering entity.
frameExamples: He <t>ranks</t> second in his class in mathematics.
It's rumored that she <t>downed</t> a helicopter with a precisely fired arrow.
McNamara <t>addressed</t> congress on the state of affairs of the Department of Defense.
Urban areas have> a higher teen suicide <t><fex name='Ratio'>rate</fex></t> than rural areas.
I'm on the <t>summit</t> of Mt. Shasta.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Rank</fen> which the <fen>Item</fen> occupies.
The Item which occupies the Rank in the hierarchy.
The dimension along which the ranking is defined.
The time at which/period over which the <fen>Item</fen> occupies the <fen>Rank</fen>
The <fen>Agent</fen> forces the <fen>Patient</fen> to come to the ground.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is being forced to the ground.
An event which causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to come to the ground.
The time at which the event takes place.
The location at which the event takes place.
The Rank itself, usually denoted by the noun.
An entity which holds a particular <fen>Rank</fen>.
The person or persons to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> delivers their text.
The person who orally delivers a text about a <fen>Topic</fen> to a passive <fen>Audience</fen>.
What the text that the <fen>Speaker</fen> produces is about.
The <fen>Time</fen> describes when the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the speaking occurs.
A representation of the conditions upon which membership to a <fen>Subset</fen> of a <fen>Group</fen> is determined.
The members of a <fen>Group</fen> that fulfill particular <fen>Criteria</fen> to belong to a <fen>Subset</fen> of the <fen>Group</fen>.
The numerical representation of the size of the <fen>Subset</fen> relative to the size of the <fen>Group</fen>.
A stable bounded area defined by its relation to another landform. This role is incorporated in each LU in this frame.
The landform with respect to which the <fen>Focal_feature</fen> is defined.
listRoleExamples: He ranks second in his class <fex>in mathematics</fex>.
Jim ranked as thirty-second degree Mason <fex>in 1970</fex>.
He lectured <fex>to the officers of the Scots Guard</fex>  in  1929.
<fex>You</fex> have to sermonize about the good times
He was the Director: he could lecture <fex>on whomever he liked</fex>.
This drug can reduce the rate <fex>of heart diseas</fex>e significantly in people over 50.
California has a high <fex>divorce</fex> rate compared to other states.
New laws have raised crime rates <fex>by 5%</fex>
